  <title translate="true">Class Diagram Pane_Summary</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal Head"><text styleclass="Normal Head" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Diagram Pane</text><text styleclass="Normal Head" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> d</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">raws a diagram for the class hierarchy surrounding the currently selected class. This will show the classes in the superclass chain and all of the subclass tree. If you click over a class in the diagram this will become the selected class in the browser.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:9pt;" translate="true">You can expand and collapse the nodes in the tree using the [+] and [-] buttons next to each class icon.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Notes"><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">Class Diagram Pane</text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true"> is a class browser plug-in and is implemented by the </text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">ClassDiagramPlugIn</text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true"> class in the image.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
